The two toggles are independent ‚Äî turning off images on Mac doesn't silence ASCII in remote sessions, and vice versa. ASCII defaults to on because it's just inline text, not a disruptive Preview flash.

### Picking the right surface

Run this check once at the start of each session and remember the result:

```bash
[ -n "${CLAUDECODE_REMOTE:-}" ] || ! command -v sips >/dev/null 2>&1 && echo "remote" || echo "mac"
```

- **`remote`** (cloud container, iPad, no Mac binaries): use the ASCII path. Display it with the `Read` tool ‚Äî it renders as plain text inline. Don't attempt the Preview flash; `sips`/`open`/`osascript` don't exist.
- **`mac`** + Warp terminal: use the image path with the Preview flash pattern below (Warp doesn't render images inline).
- **`mac`** + iTerm2 / native Terminal: use the image path with `Read` ‚Äî images render inline there.

### Preview flash (Mac + Warp only)

```bash
sips -Z 256 <image_path> --out /tmp/alfie-flash.png && \
open /tmp/alfie-flash.png && \
sleep 0.5 && \
osascript -e 'tell application "Preview" to set bounds of front window to {1152, 672, 1408, 928}' && \
sleep 2 && \
osascript -e 'quit app "Preview"'
```

The bounds `{1152, 672, 1408, 928}` center a 256√ó256 window on a 2560√ó1600 screen. This flashes the image for 2 seconds then closes Preview automatically.

Don't repeat the same Alfie twice in a row in the same session ‚Äî rotate through variants. Generate fresh images with Gemini when the set feels stale: see `~/.claude/memory/alfie-character/CHARACTER.md`. The ASCII set is fixed ‚Äî edit the `.txt` files in `~/.claude/memory/alfie-character/ascii/` if you want to refresh them.

