## Development Methodology

### The Flow ‚Äî ALWAYS follow this:
1. `/brainstorm` ‚Äî explore what to build through dialogue, produce approved design spec (saves to `docs/specs/`)
2. `/plan <name>` ‚Äî turn the spec into an implementation plan (saves to `docs/plans/`)
3. `/autoplan` ‚Äî run the full CEO/design/eng/DX review gauntlet on the plan with auto-decisions. Recommended before every build.
4. `/build <name>` ‚Äî the foreman reads the plan, routes automatically:
   - **‚â§2 tasks or tightly coupled** ‚Üí `/work` (sequential, interactive, TDD)
   - **3+ independent tasks** ‚Üí `/orchestrate` (worktree-isolated subagents, two-stage review)
5. `/qa` ‚Äî test the running app with the gstack browser. Finds and fixes bugs before review.
6. `/review` ‚Äî structured P1/P2/P3 code review of the branch
7. `/ship` ‚Äî create PR, bump VERSION, update CHANGELOG, merge
8. `/canary` ‚Äî post-deploy monitoring loop. Watch for errors after deploy.
9. `/codify <topic>` ‚Äî write a learning to `docs/solutions/`
10. `/done <name>` ‚Äî close the loop (release notes, cleanup, recap)

**Shortcuts:**
- When {{NAME}} provides a spec and says "plan this", start with `/plan`
- When {{NAME}} provides a plan and says "implement", start with `/build`
- When implementation is finished, run `/done`
- Use `/review` and `/codify` as needed along the way
- For small, well-defined bug fixes, `/brainstorm` can be skipped ‚Äî go straight to `/investigate` or `/plan`

**Direct overrides** (bypass the foreman):
- `/work <name>` ‚Äî force sequential, interactive mode
- `/orchestrate <name>` ‚Äî force parallel subagent mode with worktree isolation

### Remote / iPad session adjustments

Reuse the same remote check as the Alfie image section (`$CLAUDECODE_REMOTE` set OR no `sips` on PATH). When the session is **remote**:

- **Step 4 `/build` routing:** default to `/work` even when the plan has 3+ independent tasks. `/orchestrate`'s multi-worktree subagent output is hard to follow on small screens, and the cloud container has no Warp panes to fan out into. {{NAME}} can still force `/orchestrate <name>` explicitly.
- **Step 5 `/qa` and Step 8 `/canary`:** both depend on the gstack browser, which isn't available in cloud containers. `/build` Step 1.5 already detects remote sessions and splits these out into `docs/plans/<plan>-mac-followup.md`. Don't try to invoke `/qa` or `/canary` directly in a remote session ‚Äî point {{NAME}} at the follow-up plan, or suggest kicking them off via Claude Dispatch from iPhone to the home Mac.
- **Session Naming:** propose a session title (no "Warp tab" framing).

Everything else in the 10-step flow runs unchanged. `/brainstorm`, `/plan`, `/autoplan`, `/build ‚Üí /work`, `/review`, `/ship`, `/codify`, `/done`, and Notion auto-publish all work the same on iPad as on Mac.

### Discipline Skills (kick in at specific moments):
- `/investigate` ‚Äî systematic root cause debugging. Use before proposing fixes for any bug or test failure. No fixes without root cause.
- `/verify` ‚Äî verification before claiming done. Run tests and show output before saying "it works". Evidence before assertions.
- `/receive-review` ‚Äî process code review feedback with rigor. No sycophantic agreement. Verify claims before implementing.

### TDD Iron Law
No production code without a failing test first. If code is written before the test, delete it and start over. Every task during `/work` starts with a failing test.

### Auto-Publish to Notion
After completing `/brainstorm`, `/plan`, `/codify`, or `/done`:
1. Read `~/.claude/memory/project-registry.md` and look up the current working directory
2. If found: confirm briefly ‚Äî "Publishing to [Project] ‚Üí [Section]." ‚Äî then publish
3. Create a **database row** in the correct section using `mcp__notion-personal__notion-create-pages` with `data_source_id` parent
4. **Link relations** ‚Äî connect the new row to related rows (see relation-linking below)
5. Include the Notion link in the completion message
6. If NOT found in registry: skip silently (not every directory is a registered project)

**Publishing targets (all are databases):**
- `/brainstorm` ‚Üí Specs DB (Name: `[Topic] Design`, Status: `Draft`)
- `/plan` ‚Üí Plans DB (Name: `[Topic]`, Status: `Active`)
- `/codify` ‚Üí Learnings DB (Name: `[Topic]`, Category: pick best fit)
- `/done` ‚Üí Release Notes DB (Name: `Release [date] ‚Äî [Name]`, Date: today)

**Relation-linking (REQUIRED):**
The four databases have relation properties connecting them. Always populate these:
- `/plan` ‚Üí set **Spec** relation to the spec page it was planned from
- `/codify` ‚Üí set **Plan** relation on the learning to the active plan; also update the plan's **Learnings** relation
- `/done` ‚Üí set **Plan** relation on the release note to the plan; also update the plan's **Release Note** relation

**How to find related pages:** If the related page was created in the current session, use the saved URL. If from a prior session, query the relevant Notion database by name to find the matching row before linking.

